review_blob: bottle, medium-dark amber, thought i must say i was surprised at the tiny head. Very nice malty aroma with a nice tang. mildly hoppy with a nice fruity twine.
Bottled, nice to look at, very seasonal flavour almost like a christmas cake, verry nutty and fruity. A great beer!
First tried this a few weeks ago just as winter was setting in, gorgeous aromas reminiscent of a very pure dark chocolate, nice dark body, packs a nice winter punch.
